<p style='margin-bottom:12.0pt'>The Dependable Computing Systems research group
is focusing on building distributed systems that are tolerant to natural
failures and malicious intrusions. The research areas encompass networking,
distributed middleware and interesting applications in ad-hoc and sensor
networks. We are located in room 34 of the Electrical Engineering building (5
Linux machines and 2 PCs). Our sensor network testbeds are located in Physics
50 (8 Mica motes and 1 PC) and in Civil G239 (16 Mica2 motes and 2 PCs). </p>

